```latex
\text{"gerade } \cdot \text{ ungerade = ungerade"} \\
u(x) \text{ sei gerade } : u(-x) = u(x) \\
v(x) \text{ sei ungerade } : v(-x) = -v(x) \\
f(x) = u(x) \cdot v(x) \\
f(-x) = u(-x) \cdot v(-x) = u(x) (-v(x)) = \underbrace{-u(x) v(x)}_{f(x)} \\
\Rightarrow f(-x) = -f(x)
```

```latex
\text{"ungerade } \cdot \text{ ungerade = gerade"} \\
$u(x) \text{ sei ungerade } : u(-x) = -u(x)$ \\
$v(x) \text{ sei ungerade } : v(-x) = -v(x)$ \\
$f(x) = u(x) \cdot v(x)$ \\
$f(-x) = u(-x) \cdot v(-x) = (-u(x)) \cdot (-v(x)) = u(x) v(x)$ \\
$\Rightarrow f(-x) = f(x)$ \\
$\Rightarrow f(x)$ ist auch gerade
```

messages.content:
```desmos-graph
width: 600
height: 400

# Define points
x_1 = 1
y_1 = 2
x_2 = 4
y_2 = 4

# Calculate slope and y-intercept
m = (y_2 - y_1) / (x_2 - x_1)
n = y_1 - m * x_1

# The function f(x)
f(x) = m * x + n {x >= -1 and x <= 5}
f.label = "$f(x)$"
f.color = "#000000"

# Points P1 and P2
P_1 = (x_1, y_1)
P_1.label = "$P_1$"
P_1.color = "#000000"

P_2 = (x_2, y_2)
P_2.label = "$P_2$"
P_2.color = "#000000"

# Dashed lines for coordinates
segment((x_1, 0), P_1){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}
segment((x_2, 0), P_2){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}
segment((0, y_1), P_1){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}
segment((0, y_2), P_2){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}

# Dashed lines for Delta x and Delta y visualization
segment(P_1, (x_2, y_1)){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}
segment((x_2, y_1), P_2){lineStyle: DOTTED, color: "#000000"}

# Coordinate labels on axes
text("$$x_1$$", (x_1, -0.5), color: "#000000")
text("$$x_2$$", (x_2, -0.5), color: "#000000")
text("$$y_1$$", (-0.5, y_1), color: "#000000")
text("$$y_2$$", (-0.5, y_2), color: "#000000")

# Delta x and Delta y labels
text("$$\\Delta x = x_2 - x_1$$", ((x_1 + x_2) / 2, y_1 - 0.7), color: "#000000")
text("$$\\Delta y = y_2 - y_1$$", (x_2 + 0.7, (y_1 + y_2) / 2), color: "#000000")

# Angle alpha (requires a bit of approximation for visual arc and label)
alpha_rad = atan(m)
r_arc = 0.5 # Radius of the arc

arc_x(t) = r_arc * cos(t) + x_1
arc_y(t) = r_arc * sin(t) + y_1
(arc_x(t), arc_y(t)) {0 <= t <= alpha_rad} {color: "#000000"}

# Label for alpha
text("$$\\alpha$$", (x_1 + r_arc * cos(alpha_rad / 2 + 0.1), y_1 + r_arc * sin(alpha_rad / 2 + 0.1)), color: "#000000")
```
